author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: An all-party delegation revealed that the India-Pakistan truce on May 10 was initiated by Pakistan, dismissing claims of third-party mediation. JDU MP Sanjay Kumar Jha stated that the Pakistani DGMO's call for a ceasefire faced hotline issues, leading to communication through their embassy in India.
title: 'Pak DGMO called but problem with hotline': All-party delegation on how truce was reached

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Heavy rainfall in North Sikkim has triggered landslides and caused the Teesta River to wash away a key section of the under-construction Sankalang Bridge, severing links to remote areas. A red alert is in place as rescue teams search for nine missing tourists after a vehicle plunged into the river. Multiple properties were damaged, and travel advisories have been issued.
title: Sikkim bridge washes away as Teesta River swells amid heavy rainfall

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Apple is significantly increasing iPhone production in India, with exports to the U.S. surging by 76% in April 2025. This shift is driven by geopolitical tensions and U.S. tariffs, despite President Trump's pressure to relocate manufacturing to the U.S. However, analysts warn that U.S.-based production would drastically increase costs, making India a crucial part of Apple's global strategy.
title: Top Apple analyst does not want Apple to listen to Trump’s 25% tariff warning

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A remarkable video from South Goa has captured the hearts of social media users, showcasing an extraordinary football match between a young boy and a crow. The bird skillfully uses its beak to pass the ball back and forth, creating an adorable and captivating display of interspecies teamwork.
title: Watch: Goa crow shows off football skills, internet wants to sign him up

author: AMIT BHATTACHARYA
description: Delhi recorded its wettest May since 1901, reflecting a sharp rise in rainfall over decades—tripling since 1951. Recent years saw an average of 95.7mm rain, yet temperatures remain unchanged. Experts link the trend to increased thunderstorms and moisture from global warming. Rising humidity heightens health risks, power demand, and infrastructure stress, signaling a significant climate shift.
title: How Delhi's summer is changing: 3-fold rise in May rainfall in 75 years

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Imagine Dragons' Dan Reynolds ignited controversy by kissing a Palestinian flag during a Milan concert, sparking accusations of supporting extremism and betraying pro-Israel fans. The act drew both outrage and support, highlighting the band's complicated history with the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, including a previous performance in Tel Aviv and waving a Ukrainian flag during the same concert.
title: Watch: Imagine Dragons' Dan Reynolds kisses Palestinian flag on stage

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Paris Saint-Germain fans celebrated their Champions League victory, resulting in nearly 600 arrests due to clashes with police near the Champs-Elysees. A car incident in Grenoble injured four celebrating fans. Despite the unrest, joyous fans sang and danced, celebrating PSG's historic win. President Macron will host the team, and a victory parade is planned on the Champs-Elysees.
title: PSG UCL celebrations turn tragic: Two dead, 559 arrested across France

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A new COVID-19 strain, NB.1.8.1, is under scrutiny as Washington state reports its first case. Simultaneously, the CDC has updated its vaccine guidance, now allowing, but not mandating, COVID-19 vaccines for healthy children based on clinical judgment. This shift follows a directive from Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr., raising concerns among health officials about evidence-based decision-making.
title: Covid in US: Kids now 'may receive' COVID-19 vaccines

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Pawan Kalyan has denounced the arrest of a Symbiosis law student for allegedly hurting religious sentiments through a viral video during ‘Operation Sindoor’. He criticized the silence surrounding alleged blasphemy by TMC leaders and MPs, accusing them of mocking Sanatana Dharma. The student was remanded to judicial custody, and Symbiosis International University suspended her, distancing itself from her comments.
title: ‘Secularism must be two-way street’: Kalyan slams student's arrest by WB Police

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Elon Musk refuted claims of frequent ketamine use, dismissing a New York Times report as false. He admitted to using prescription ketamine years ago for mental health but denies current usage. This denial follows a report alleging daily use and potential health impacts.
title: Tesla CEO Elon Musk admits: ‘I am NOT taking drugs, I tried….’

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Amidst stricter student visa regulations and political uncertainties in the US, Indian students and their families are increasingly exploring the EB-5 visa option for permanent residency. Applications from F-1 visa holders have surged, driven by concerns over potential disruptions to their academic pursuits and future prospects.
title: Trump crackdown on student visas: Here’s what Indians are doing

author: Agencies
title: Hamas agrees to free 10 hostages alive; says war must end

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: During closing arguments, a federal judge challenged Google's defense against antitrust remedies, expressing skepticism about the company's stance on AI restrictions and search dominance. The Justice Department seeks to limit Google's AI ambitions, viewing AI as the future of search, while Google plans to appeal the ruling expected in August, regardless of the outcome.
title: Judge to Google asking not to restrict its reach in AI: What you are telling is …

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Michelle Obama's recent remarks on her podcast, stating that creating life is "the least" of what a woman's reproductive system does, have sparked controversy. She emphasised the broader importance of women's reproductive health beyond just procreation, criticising the lack of medical research and political decision-making on the issue. Conservative figures and social media users have strongly condemned her comments.
title: Michelle Obama says 'creating life is the least' a woman's body does, faces heat

author: PRATYUSH RAJ
description: Jasprit Bumrah rarely shows emotion on the pitch and seldom celebrates a wicket, but in the IPL 2025 Eliminator, he looked like a man possessed. He finished with 1/27 in four overs — below par by his standards — yet Washington Sundar’s wicket turned the tide in MI’s favour. In a world where bowlers get their due beyond talk shows and podcasts, Bumrah might well have pipped Rohit for the Player of the Match award.
title: PBKS' biggest challenge: How to survive 'possessed' Bumrah's 24 balls

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The UK's defence review identifies Russia as an immediate threat and China as a persistent challenge, drawing lessons from the Ukraine war. Britain faces a new era of warfare with emerging technologies.
title: Russia an 'immediate' threat, China a 'sophisticated' one: UK defence review warns

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A wedding celebration in Jhansi descended into chaos when a dispute over a cooler ignited a violent clash between the bride's and groom's families. The argument began when guests from the groom's side sat in front of a cooler meant for the wedding couple, leading to objections from the bride's family.
title: Watch: Chairs fly as wedding guests brawl over cooler in Jhansi

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Guwahati experienced severe waterlogging due to incessant rainfall, leading to rescue operations by various agencies. The city recorded its highest-ever May rainfall, intensifying the impact of a depression over Bangladesh and Meghalaya. Tragically, several fatalities were reported across northeastern states, including Assam, due to floods and landslides, prompting ongoing evacuation and relief efforts.
title: Watch: Guwahati submerged as heavy rain causes severe waterlogging

author: ASHNI DHAOR
description: In Greater Noida, a liquor salesman, Manish Kumar, alleges that excise inspector Chandra Shekhar assaulted him for overcharging customers. Kumar claims he was slapped, beaten with a belt, and detained at the excise office. His family protested after police refused to register a complaint.
title: Salesman slapped, thrashed with belt for charging Rs 10 extra on beer in Noida

author: PRATYUSH RAJ
description: Punjab Kings bowler Yuzvendra Chahal, who is nursing a wrist injury, and Mumbai Indians' seamer Deepak Chahar, who didn't play the Eliminator against Gujarat Titans due to a hamstring niggle, are likely to play for their respective teams in Qualifier 2 at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad.
title: IPL 2025 Qualifier 2: Punjab Kings likely to get Yuzvendra Chahal boost

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru, under Rajat Patidar's leadership, have reached the IPL 2025 final, defeating Punjab Kings. Dinesh Karthik's role as batting coach is drawing attention, with predictions of exuberant celebrations if RCB win their first title. Karthik's coaching has already shown positive results, and he expresses a strong connection to the team and a desire to contribute to their success.
title: 'Unbearable': Why Nasser, Atherton don't want RCB to win IPL 2025

author: RIYAN RAMANATH V
description: Baikunthanath Sarangi, a chief engineer, was arrested on his retirement day for amassing disproportionate assets exceeding Rs 15 crore. He was caught on video throwing cash during a vigilance raid. Searches revealed multiple properties, significant cash holdings, and investments. In a separate case, searches were conducted on N Dillip Kumar Choudhury, an assistant executive engineer, for similar allegations.
title: Odisha engineer held on retirement day for assets worth Rs 15 cr, 483% more than income

author: AJAY SINGH UGRAS
description: Valmik Thapar, a renowned conservationist, author, and documentarian, passed away at 73 after dedicating 50 years to tiger conservation in India. His encounter with Fateh Singh Rathore in Ranthambhore ignited a lifelong mission to protect tigers, leading to the establishment of the Ranthambhore Foundation and influencing national wildlife policy.
title: Valmik Thapar walked with tigers, now he rests

author: AFP
description: A bus crash on a Nigerian highway on Saturday killed 21 athletes returning from a national sports tournament, with authorities saying the accident might have been the result of driver fatigue or excessive speed. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) said the afternoon crash, which did not involve other vehicles, "might have occurred as a result of fatigue and excessive speed" after a long overnight trip.
title: 21 athletes killed in Nigeria road crash

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill and Hardik Pandya have dismissed rumours of a rift following Gujarat Titans' IPL 2025 elimination, addressing speculation fuelled by on-field interactions and Pandya's move to Mumbai Indians. Both players affirmed their camaraderie on social media after Mumbai Indians' victory in the Eliminator match. Mumbai Indians will play IPL Qualifier 2 against Punjab Kings today.
title: After Gill, Pandya also shuts down rumours of rift between the two

author: RAJIV KALKOD
description: Bengaluru police solved the mystery of Gangadharaiah's death, initially deemed unnatural. An autopsy revealed fractured ribs, leading to a murder investigation. The break came when the victim's stolen mobile phone was activated in Salem, Tamil Nadu. Police traced it to Naresh Kumar Raja, a wanted criminal, who confessed to attacking and robbing Gangadharaiah, resulting in his death.
title: He robbed truck driver in Bengaluru, but didn’t know his punches killed victim

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Elon Musk refuted claims of extensive drug use, including ketamine, during the 2024 Presidential campaign, labeling a New York Times report as false. He admitted to a past prescription for ketamine to combat mental health issues but stated he hasn't used it recently. The report alleged Musk's drug use led to health problems and cited erratic behavior.
title: 'I am not taking drugs!': Musk refutes claims of drug abuse during 2024 campaign trail

author: AFP
description: Luis Enrique celebrated Paris Saint-Germain's emphatic 5-0 Champions League victory over Inter Milan, fulfilling the club's long-sought ambition since the 2011 Qatari takeover. He dedicated the win to his late daughter, Xana, acknowledging the emotional tribute from PSG fans. Enrique also lauded Ousmane Dembele's performance, suggesting he deserves the Ballon d'Or.
title: PSG fans honour Enrique's daughter, who died from cancer, with banner

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Rajkummar Rao and Wamiqa Gabbi's 'Bhool Chuk Maaf' is a box office success after its theatrical release on May 23, 2025. The film earned ₹5.15 crore on its second Saturday, bringing the total to ₹52.50 crore. Despite mixed reviews, audiences are enjoying the time-loop romantic drama set in Banaras, which follows Ranjan's quest for love and a government job.
title: 'Bhool Chuk Maaf': Rajkummar Rao, Wamiqa Gabbi’s starrer earns over Rs 5cr on day 9

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following his expulsion from the RJD and estrangement from his father, Lalu Prasad Yadav, Tej Pratap Yadav has publicly appealed to his parents for their love and trust, blaming political conspiracies for his downfall. Lalu expelled Tej Pratap for allegedly violating moral values and harming the family's principles after a controversial social media post.
title: 'Dear mom & dad ... ': Tej Pratap pleads for love, blames ‘greedy people’ for rift with family

author: BAGISH JHA
description: In Gurgaon's Ridgewood Estate, concerned neighbors alerted authorities to the plight of an elderly couple allegedly abandoned by their son living abroad. The Haryana Human Rights Commission intervened, ordering a comprehensive assessment after residents reported the couple's distress and lack of proper care.
title: Elderly couple ‘abandoned’ in their Gurgaon flat for 3 years, community steps in

author: SIDHARTHA
description: The Indian government is considering raising the safeguard duty on steel to 24% from the existing 12% due to concerns about potential circumvention by Chinese companies and the impact on domestic steelmakers. This move comes amid fears of trade diversion as Chinese goods face increased levies in other markets, potentially leading to dumping in India.
title: Government mulls doubling safeguard duty on steel from 12% to 24%

author: etimes.in
description: Aly Goni and Jasmin Bhasin have moved into their new home, a decision celebrated by their fans. Aly shared his reaction to Jasmin's interior design choices in a vlog, showcasing their home's features, including separate kitchens for vegetarian and non-vegetarian guests.
title: Jasmin Bhasin reveals she designed their home exactly as Aly Goni's dream

author: RAJAT PANDIT
description: CDS Gen Anil Chauhan highlighted that India spent 15% of Operation Sindoor's time countering disinformation during the four-day conflict with Pakistan, which he termed a "non-contact and multi-domain" war. India maintained operational clarity and autonomy, detecting no unusual Chinese activity along the LAC. The nation relied on indigenous systems and drew a new redline against Pakistani terrorism, emphasizing fact-based communication.
title: Spent 15% of time nixing fake news during Op Sindoor: CDS

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Mario Nawfal shared a Newsweek excerpt revealing Russia's plummeting birth rate, hitting a 200-year low, now deemed a state secret. Elon Musk responded, noting that declining birth rates are a global issue. Russia is implementing measures like banning 'childfree ideology' and offering incentives to boost its population, which could drop significantly by 2045.
title: Elon Musk responds to what is claimed to be Russia's 'State secret': Almost all ...

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A passenger train derailed in Russia's Bryansk region after a bridge collapsed, resulting in at least seven fatalities and 30 injuries. Russian authorities attribute the incident to "illegal interference," citing damage to the bridge above the railway line. The collapse sent debris onto the tracks, impacting the oncoming train, with emergency services responding to the scene.
title: 7 killed, 30 injured as passenger train derails after bridge collapse in Russia

author: RASHMI DROLIA
description: Following the death of Maoist commander Basavaraju, Devji's granddaughter, Itlu Suma Tipiri, has made an emotional appeal for him to surrender. In a video message, Suma urges her grandfather, a potential successor to Basavaraju, to return home. She questions the state's anti-Maoist operations while expressing the family's longing for his return.
title: ‘Grandpa, come home’: Granddaughter of top Maoist commander Devji makes appeal

author: VISHVENDU JAIPURIAR AND ABHIJIT SEN
description: A surrendered Maoist, Chhota Shyamlal Dehri, who was incarcerated in Hazaribag jail since 2021, allegedly committed suicide in his cell on Saturday. He used a rope and wire to hang himself from the ceiling fan. Jail authorities discovered the incident during the morning count, raising questions about how he obtained the rope.
title: Surrendered Maoist dies by suicide in Hazaribag jail

author: JOY SENGUPTA
description: SpiceJet's Delhi-Pune flight SG-477, carrying approximately 150 passengers, reached its destination nearly four hours late on Friday. The flight, initially scheduled for a 3:25 pm departure, faced delays due to a last-minute technical issue. Passengers were kept waiting inside the aircraft for around three hours, causing frustration.
title: Spicejet fliers forced to sit in aircraft for 3 hours in Delhi
